  "description": [
    "Monday August 2 1948 ii I I I Meet Adopts Minimum Civil Rights Program WASHINGTON Aug 2 AN PA five point minimum pro gram for civil rights legislation was adopted here recently by representatives of 25 national la bor civil rights fraternal Negro and religious organizations attend ing a conference held at the Wil lard hotel The conference called by the NAACP recommended enactment by the special session of congress of legislation for a permanent FEPC abolition of the poll tax puntive measures to suppress lynching and mob violence ban ning of segregation in interstate transportation and revision of the displaced persons act to permit immigration of classes now dis criminated against The conference also urged that President Truman issue immediate ly an executive order banning dis crimination and segregation in the federal services including the armed forces The statement pointed out that The special session gives the 80th congress a third chance to fulfill the urgent needs of the American people The congress can now com plete the business left unfinished on its calendar and make a gen uine contribution to the freedom and equality of all Americans by 5DAY GUARANTEED WATCH REPAIR SERVICE ALL MAKE CRYSTALS IDAY SERVICE"
  ],
